  "texts": [
    "As an individual interacts with environment and observes it accordingly, policy regarding usage of generative AI should focus on structural dilemmas of scientific publishing, predating the emergence of generative AI.",
    "Generative AI in this context represents an irritation exemplifying that there are structural problems in the process of scientific production and scientific authorship in the first place not only because of technology or individuals intentionally or unintentionally bypassing the rules, procedures, and establish practices.",
    "If solutions are to be found, authorship should be perceived as an autopoietic system described above-as a relational phenomenon which is not deterministic on one specific ingredient.",
    "Therefore, to blame technology or human agency and leave the things as they are would be further augmenting existing power relations as well as the status quo of inertia which is not compatible with the \"nature\" of science.",
    "Therefore, it is not about regulation of technology alone, but about relational dynamics which can then change the ways of dealing with certain social and societal issues."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}